{"lemma":"نَبَطُ","slug":"نَبَطُ","root":"ن.ب.ط","root_slug":"ن-ب-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ب-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39253","","n39256"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39253","headword_ar":"نَبَطَ","root":"nbT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nubuwTN","text_ar":"نُبُوطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naboTN","text_ar":"نَبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(water)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"welled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"issued forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)       -A2-  See also 4."}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n39256","headword_ar":"نَبَطٌ","root":"nbT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What first appears of the water of a well"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is dug;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuboTapN","text_ar":"نُبْطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the water that comes forth from a well when it is first dug:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water that issues forth from the bottom of a well when it is dug;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, accord. to one copy;) or this is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiyTN","text_ar":"نَبِيطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, accord. to another copy; and TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anobaATN","text_ar":"اَنْبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nubuwTN","text_ar":"نُبُوطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN qariybu Alv~araY baEiydu Aln~abaTi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ قَرِيبُ الثَّرَى بَعِيدُ النَّبَطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one's promising is near,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his fulfilling is remote:"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he promises, but does not fulfil."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"flAn laA yudoraku nabaTuhu","text_ar":"فلان لَا يُدْرَكُ نَبَطُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yudoraku lahu nabaTN","text_ar":"لَا يُدْرَكُ لَهُ نَبَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISd, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one's depth is not known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the extent of his knowledge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one's depth is not known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning that he is cunning, or possessing intelligence mixed with craft and forecast. (ISd, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA yunaAlu nabaTuhu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا يُنَالُ نَبَطُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is invincible, and inaccessible to his enemy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaTN","text_ar":"نَبَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well of which the water has been produced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fetched out, by labour"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the digger"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What oozes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exudes, from a mountain, as though it were sweat, coming forth from the sides of the rock."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~abaTu","text_ar":"النَّبَطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~abiyTu","text_ar":"النَّبِيطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^anobaATu","text_ar":"الاَنْبَاطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) the last is a pl. (AAF, S, Msb) of the first, (AAF,) and the second is [a quasi-pl. n.] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliybN","text_ar":"كَلِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AAF, L,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Nabathæans;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a people who alight and abide in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTaAy^iH","text_ar":"بَطَايِح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboTaHu","text_ar":"اَبْطَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the two 'Iráks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a people"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Mgh, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who alight and abide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who used to alight and abide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAd","text_ar":"سَوَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Mgh, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of El- 'Irák:"},{"kind":"text","text":") (M, Mgh, Msb:) afterwards applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mixed people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people of the lowest"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basest"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2760},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meanest sort;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the refuse of men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the vulgar sort thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) the people to whom these appellations properly apply were called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaT","text_ar":"نَبَط"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of their fetching out by labour ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA@sotinobaATihimo","text_ar":"لِا@سْتِنْبَاطِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":") what comes forth from the lands: (TA:) [for they were distinguished for agriculture; and hence their proper appellations are used as equivalent to “ clowns, ” or “ boors: ” but a derivation commonly obtaining with us is that from Nebaioth the son of Ishmael:] the n. un. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nubaATiY~N","text_ar":"نُبَاطِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Yaakoob, IAar, S, Mgh, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaATiY~N","text_ar":"نَبَاطِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, S, Msb, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamaAniY~N","text_ar":"يَمَانِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nibaATiY~N","text_ar":"نِبَاطِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaATK","text_ar":"نَبَاطٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamaAnK","text_ar":"يَمَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaTiY~N","text_ar":"نَبَطِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamaniY~N","text_ar":"يَمَنِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) but this is disallowed by IAar, (Mgh, TA,) and, accord. to Lth, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaTaAniY~N","text_ar":"نَبَطَانِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this [also] is disallowed by IAar. (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["IDrd","K","Zj","TA","ISd","S","Mgh","Msb","AAF","L","T","M","IAar"]}]}}